{"key":"post-9580229","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9580229</id>\n<content>You can't &lt;i&gt;pasteurize&lt;/i&gt; in a microwave.&amp;nbsp; All you can do is superheat the material.&amp;nbsp; You'll have more success if you'll mix all your ingredients, moisturize to field capacity, and then heat until the center of the substrate is at 140F to 160F for one hour.&amp;nbsp; If you can pull that off in a microwave, go for it, but there's far easier and better ways to pasteurize.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9580261</next>\n<prev>9580191</prev>\n<first>9580191</first>\n<last>9581692</last>\n<when>1231566082</when>\n<utime>01/10/09 07:41 AM</utime>\n</post>"}